annotation.TEXT: Okay, now this guy doesn't have a mouth, but he can still shoot at you. He starts off firing single aimed shots at you, which are easy to dodge.
Oh, yeah. I remember this level, where I pointed out to the developer a way you could get trapped at the beginning, so the dev added a one-way panel there to prevent that.
However, what if we could get the metal box onto the yellow gate? Would there be a point in doing that?

And, don't forget to vote on costumes as well. But, don't try to be silly or cryptic with your costume votes. Just say what costumes you want directly. Okay, now for 2-8 Time Attack with... Fairy Mira, I guess.
Oh, be very careful NOT to hit any of the gate switches up there yet, or you'll screw yourself out of the gem in the upper-right.
I really do wonder what kinds of combos I could get in this level with Mira...

Alright, clearing 5-C doesn't unlock any new levels, so it's time for the boss level next! It's Irvette's turn, and there were no costume votes for her, so I'll just go with whatever's next in the sequence.
Nuts... I was there, and then I derpily thrust myself back onto the conveyor. Now I have to wait for it to take me all the way to its right side before I can rest...
At 60% damage, anger phase 3 starts. The barrage is gonna get quite intense now, but you can just follow the spiral pattern like this.
Ack. Whatever.

Ah, yep. They're kind of like the "solid-only-for-the-player" custom blocks in Mario hacks, so the metal box can fall right through. Oh, and the conveyor works as expected, pushing the box onto the gate switch.
Now, I'm not killing that guy yet because I want to include him in a combo in a moment, but I have to deal with a green button first.
Of course, maybe Mira or perhaps Irvette could get better use out of using the conveyors to preserve combos, but whatever. Anyway, let's take a look at this setup over here...
...and land here, but that won't do us any good. We could then shove it towards the green switch, but that's already active anyway, so there's no point in that.
It could be done, by shooting the box to make it go right while it's on this conveyor, but that's gonna be tricky, especially with Daria. However, it is something that needs to be done.
This last guy might be tricky...
Now, it looks like beating 6-1 will unlock two more levels, one straight to the east, and one to the southeast. I guess you guys could vote on which path I follow after I beat 6-1.
Fortunately, he's close enough for Irvette to hit from the floor. So, yeah, just shoot him while sidestepping his shots. As per the norm, at 20% damage, he enters his first anger mode.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Brutal combo! (6 kills, 10,500 points)

If this box falls off of the left side of this conveyor, then I will have failed, and the gem will be unreachable. I must do my best to send the box to the right, onto the yellow gate, and Daria's mana consumption won't make this easy.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Owow... It's okay. I can still get a full combo, and there'll be a health potion in the boss's room.
So, it's unanimous for 5-C, and since it's Daria's turn (which I double-checked this time), I'll go with the raincoat costume of course.

No problem. But, for normal phase 4, he's added a defensive measure, preventing you from targeting him from the floor now. This makes things quite a bit trickier. However, he's only firing single shots during this phase.

Now, for normal phase 2, he now fires a 3-way shot, with the center one aimed at you. Unless you're flying wildly around, you shouldn't need to worry about the two outer shots, so just focus on sidestepping the middle one.
Alright, this level has a couple of new features. Obviously, there's the conveyor belts, as the level name hinted at. But, there are also these thin floors with yellow "!!" labels on them.
I can't believe I got so sloppy at the end there, but it's done now.
Oh, man. A bunch of snipers, which makes sense, since this is the sniper boss level. First, go down and get these four coins if you want them, since they'll be blocked off later.
♠ush! You'll want to hit this green switch now, since there's a green further ahead.
Yeah, Daria's not gonna be getting very good combos here. Okay, now do you see this A button over here? Well, DO NOT press it.
Alright, there's a bunch of duders here, and I kinda wish I was using Mira, who would be much better at comboing here.
COINS!!! Actually, maybe I should've left those alone until later, when I could've grabbed the exact amount I needed for the 3-star bonus.
It would eventually fall down this way...
Okay, not bad, but I was a bit sloppy in a few places, so this time is certainly improvable. 7800 should be doable at least, and even 8000 might be possible.
Excellent. Okay, let's gather up the coins right there, and then it's boss time!
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Well, no matter, because as I said, it's not needed anymore, so let's just move on.
Okay, all the enemies in this level are slain, so let's examine the puzzles here now.

Unfortunately, that dev, tkhnoman, recently quit from ElagoTech apparently, so this game might not be able to receive any more changes. Let's hope it's perfectly fine as is, with no game-breaking bugs anywhere.
Alright, that'll do it for this episode! To be continued... Yo!
Yes-- NOOOOO!!!!!
Excellent. Okay, now for the last gem, which is behind that B gate.
...Seriously?! I can't believe I flew into that shot like a drunk...
Oh, pickle juice! Okay, I'm restarting now.
Aha, there we go! Oh, and it should be obvious why I needed to clear out the blocks and enemies from that conveyor belt shaft now, to make room for the metal box to get through.

To get that gem, the blue switch needs to be hit, and that requires hitting the A button. But, if you hit the A button directly, the yellow gate will close and prevent you from getting the gem. So, you gotta do this instead.

And we don't need this metal box for anything anymore... Huh, this is odd. I think this yellow gate is a tiny iota lower than the solid floor next to it, and as a result, this metal box is stuck on it now.
Yeah, Pirate Irvette is fine.
Just do little flybys like this, and rest to get your mana back on the other side. Repeat until you hit the 80% damage mark to start his fourth anger phase.
So, what do those "!!" floors do? Well, let's push a metal box onto them.
Next, hit the yellow button on the right, then quickly fly up and wait in between the gates for the box to hit the green button below, which'll open the green gate so you can get the gem.

Huzzah! Whew, there were a couple points where I thought I was in trouble. Okay, now make sure the box is pushed right up against the right wall. You don't want it to catch on the conveyor below when you open the yellow gate.
Whoa, don't get ahead of myself. I have to explain what I just unlocked first. I unlocked 6-1, which I'll be playing next time!
Okay, I'm doing quite well here. Maybe I can get a flawless victory...
At 40% damage, it's anger phase 2. He'll shoot out shots all around again, but more of them. Still should be easy to slip through.
Okay, gotta go fast! I can buy a little time by sending the box back to the left a bit while it's on this top conveyor, but I still have to book it!
Yeah, let that metal box remotely hit the A button for you while you wait in between the gates (BTW, don't run out of mana while waiting).

Maybe that might have a use with combo preservation, but since the conveyors will still move you along them, you'll likely soon find yourself landing on normal floor, so I don't think they're that helpful for combos.
Move carefully in between them, or maybe try to move quickly to dodge around the outside of them if you want. I think it's easier to go between them, though.
Woo! Yeah, that went on for a while, and does require taking to the air at least for some of it, but by starting near the lower-right corner, you can deal with most of it while on the ground.
Man, I got ridiculously sloppy. I know I can perform better than that.
Argh! Okay, whatever! Just die already!
Almost out of mana, but there is a spot I can rest at to the left of this conveyor. Can I make it there?
Well, I can still finish at full health by grabbing the health potion.
For normal phase 3, his 3-way shot becomes more focused, so there's less room to dodge in between the shots.
Well, first, we have this yellow gate, and there's also a metal box in the upper-right that we could move... Okay, so what would happen if we put the metal box on the conveyors?
And, man... if that drove me nuts, I may be dreading the next gem puzzle...
Pay attention for when his spiral switches direction!
If you hit it now, you'll lock yourself out of the second gem. However, you do need to bust the blocks and destroy the snipers above. Just be very careful not to land on that A button.
Odd thing about the conveyors-- You can't actually properly land on them with your feet. This prevents you from resting and recovering mana quickly like usual while riding on them.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)

If I were to place the metal box on the right side of the yellow gate, then hit a yellow switch above, the box would actually fall onto the green switch below, and that's necessary for the upper-right gem.
Actually, it's fine if that happens. Just open the blue gate again so you can go up and tip the box into the B basket yourself.
Oops. Well, we don't need the A button pressed anymore (though maybe I should've left it held so that it would be useful for getting the Watch for Rolling Rocks star in 0.5 A presses).
And there we go! That's all three gems, so I'm done here!
Oh, yeah. Unlocked world 5 for Time Attacking.
And there's the green button, needed to change a mirror to redirect the laser.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! Did it really stop just short of the B button like that?!
Then, fly up here and destroy these cracked blocks, then rush down and hit a yellow button to close the blue gate before the metal box falls through it!
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Okay, for this anger phase, you might want to start in the lower-right part of the room. Get ready!

Now, the final normal phase is the same as the fourth normal phase, except he's using the focused 3-way shot again. It's quite tricky, and this time, I recommend against trying to slip between them. Just fly around them entirely.
Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Okay, here are the voting results this time: 1 vote for Raincoat Daria, 0 votes for 5-BOSS, and 8 votes for 5-C!
I bet this wouldn't be nearly as bad with Mira and Irvette.
Obviously, we need something to be sitting on that B button there, and the only thing available is that one metal box above. So first, open the blue gate.
Okay, still a bit sloppy, but better than before, and I can still get that full combo.
Okay, during this anger phase, he shoots all around a few times, but you'll have plenty wide openings to slip through.
Awesome, made it! ...Wait, what?
